<item>
            <title>[LU-8323] lustre-initialization-1: fails for older servers and master clients</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8323</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue was created by maloo for parinay &amp;lt;parinay_kondekar@xyratex.com&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;This issue relates to the following test suite run: &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/b30af806-39d6-11e6-acf3-5254006e85c2&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/b30af806-39d6-11e6-acf3-5254006e85c2&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;
    trevis-8vm1 (Role_Client 1)
    trevis-8vm2 (Role_Client 2)
    trevis-8vm3 (Role_OSS 1)
    trevis-8vm4 (Role_MDS 1)
    trevis-8vm8 (Role_MDS 2)

&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;05:36:17:CMD: trevis-8vm2,trevis-8vm3,trevis-8vm4,trevis-8vm8 PATH=/usr/lib64/lustre/tests:/usr/lib/lustre/tests:/usr/lib64/lustre/tests:/opt/iozone/bin:/usr/lib64/lustre/tests/mpi:/usr/lib64/lustre/tests/racer:/usr/lib64/lustre/../lustre-iokit/sgpdd-survey:/usr/lib64/lustre/tests:/usr/lib64/lustre/utils/gss:/usr/lib64/lustre/utils:/usr/lib64/qt-3.3/bin:/usr/lib64/compat-openmpi16/bin:/usr/bin:/bin:/usr/sbin:/sbin::/sbin:/bin:/usr/sbin: NAME=autotest_config sh rpc.sh set_hostid 
05:36:18:trevis-8vm3: rpc.sh: line 20: set_hostid: command not found
05:36:18:trevis-8vm8: rpc.sh: line 20: set_hostid: command not found
05:36:18:trevis-8vm4: rpc.sh: line 20: set_hostid: command not found
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The patch for &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-7134&quot; title=&quot;Ensure ZFS hostid protection if servicenode/failover options given to mkfs.lustre&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-7134&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-7134&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is not present on b2_1. The &lt;b&gt;set_hostid()&lt;/b&gt; is not present on servers here.
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;    trevis-8vm3 (Role_OSS 1)
    trevis-8vm4 (Role_MDS 1)
    trevis-8vm8 (Role_MDS 2)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;$ git log --oneline  --grep LU-7134
7b654fc LU-7134 utils: Ensure hostid set for ZFS during mkfs
parinay@osh:~/Code/lustre-intel$ git branch --contains 7b654fc -r
  origin/HEAD -&amp;gt; origin/master
  origin/master

&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;IMO This needs to be fixed.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
